definitions.definition: An outdoor place acting as temporary accommodation in tents or other simple structures.
examples: There's a big camp in the woods northwest of here. It's popular with hikers and bushcrafters.

definitions.definition: An organised event, often taking place in tents or temporary accommodation.
examples: I met my best friend last summer at camp . She lives in Albany and plays the clarinet.
He used to go to summer camp every alternate year.
I met my girlfriend last summer at camp . You wouldn't know her — she lives in Canada.

definitions.definition: A base of a military group, not necessarily temporary.
examples: Signs of enemy recon were found near their camp last week.

definitions.definition: A place of politically motivated confinement in outdoorsy conditions, usually also leading to slave labor and death .
examples: Some say they'll round us all up into camps , but if they come for us, we'll take some out with us, on our way out.

definitions.definition: The company or body of persons encamped.
A group of people with the same strong ideals or political leanings.
examples: She's in the camp that speaks as if all vaccines were poisons.

definitions.definition: ( prison slang ) Any prison or prison camp .
( agriculture , catachresis ) Misconstruction of clamp ( “ mound of earth in which potatoes and other vegetables are stored ” ) .
( British India ) Anywhere that a colonist stayed when away from their permanent residence; such places collectively.
An online game, in some cases roleplay , in which people compete against each other, usually in a structure similar to that of a competition show .

definitions.definition: The areas of the Falkland Islands situated outside the capital and largest settlement, Stanley .
An electoral constituency of the legislative assembly of the Falkland Islands that composes of all territory more than 3.5 miles from the spire of the Christ Church Cathedral in Stanley.
